\chapter{Implementation}
\label{ch:implementation}



\lettrine[lines=2]{T}{his chapter} examines the architectural decisions, design patterns, and implementation strategies employed to translate the biological model described in preceding chapters into executable software. The discussion focuses on the engineering problems encountered during development and the design patterns used to address them, with particular attention to how computational constraints influenced biological model design.

% ======================================================================
\section{Framework Migration: Mesa to Repast4Py}
\label{sec:framework-migration}

\begin{figure}[htbp]
\centering
\adjustbox{max width=0.85\textwidth, max height=0.7\textheight}{\input{figures/architecture_overview.tex}}
\caption{Software architecture overview of the RCC simulation system}
\label{fig:architecture_overview}
\end{figure}

The migration from Mesa to Repast4Py required substantial architectural changes, detailed in Table~\ref{tab:porting-mapping}. Three design patterns structure the core simulation logic: the Command pattern, the Observer pattern, and the Strategy pattern.

The Command pattern governs agent movement. During each simulation step, agents do not move immediately upon deciding their next position. Instead, each agent stores its desired destination as a movement request. Once all agents have completed their decision phase, the model executes these requests in a batch deferred-move phase. This two-phase approach prevents order-dependent artifacts that would otherwise arise if early-moving agents altered the spatial landscape before later agents had evaluated their own neighborhoods. By decoupling the decision from the execution, the simulation produces results that are invariant to the internal iteration order over agents within a single step.

The Observer pattern decouples data collection from agent behavior. A dedicated data-collection observer records population counts by cell type, glucose field statistics (mean, minimum, standard deviation), and cumulative kill tallies at the conclusion of each simulation step. These observations are written to CSV log files independently of the agent logic itself. This separation ensures that instrumenting the simulation for analysis introduces no side effects into the model dynamics and permits the logging granularity to be modified without altering any agent class.

The Strategy pattern enables runtime selection of treatment modalities. Each treatment type---immune checkpoint inhibitor (ICI) therapy, tyrosine kinase inhibitor (TKI) therapy, and combination therapy---implements a common Drug interface exposing a \texttt{step()} method that applies the drug's per-tick effects to the simulation state. The model holds a reference to the active treatment strategy and invokes its \texttt{step()} method during the treatment phase of the main loop. Adding a new treatment modality requires only implementing the Drug interface; no modifications to the simulation core or execution pipeline are necessary.



